'''Altay Bayındır''' (born 14 April 1998) is a Turkish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|ManchesU}} club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

Bayındır began his career at [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]]. He joined [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] in July 2019, where he made 145 appearances. In September 2023, he signed for Manchester United.

Bayındır played 14 times for Turkey at youth international level. He made his senior international debut in May 2021.

==Club career==
===Ankaragücü===
Bayındır made his [[Süper Lig]] debut for [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]] in a 1–1 draw with [[Çaykur Rizespor]] on 30 November 2018.<ref name="TFF 2018 Rizespor Ankaragucu">{{cite news|title=Çaykur Rizespor – MKE Ankaragücü TFF Maç Detayı|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=194632|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|access-date=5 October 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201005093044/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=194632|archive-date=5 October 2020}}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
On 8 July 2019, Bayındır joined [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] on a four-year contract.<ref name="2019 Fenerbahce signing">{{cite news|title= Altay Bayındır Renklerimize Bağlandı|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2019/7/altay-bayindir-renklerimize-baglandi|publisher=[[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]|date=8 July 2019|access-date=5 October 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201005092829/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2019/7/altay-bayindir-renklerimize-baglandi|archive-date=5 October 2020}}</ref> Bayındır became the first-choice goalkeeper ahead of teammate [[Harun Tekin (footballer)|Harun Tekin]].<ref name="2019 Firstchoicekeeper">{{cite news|title= Avrupa'nın gözü Fenerbahçeli Altay Bayındır'ın üstünde|url=https://www.yenisafak.com/spor/avrupanin-gozu-fenerbahceli-altay-bayindirin-ustunde-3509928|publisher=[[Yeni Şafak]]|date=11 October 2019|access-date=5 October 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201005094156/https://www.yenisafak.com/spor/avrupanin-gozu-fenerbahceli-altay-bayindirin-ustunde-3509928|archive-date=5 October 2020}}</ref> On 19 August 2019, he made his Fenerbahçe debut in a 5–0 win against [[Gazişehir Gaziantep F.K.|Gaziantep]] at [[Şükrü Saracoğlu Stadium]].<ref name="TFF 2019 FB GGFK">{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe A.Ş. – Gazişehir Gaziantep Futbol Kulübü TFF Maç Detayı|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=207155|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|access-date=5 October 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201005094722/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=207155|archive-date=5 October 2020}}</ref>

On 3 October 2020, Bayındır saved a penalty from [[Erik Sabo]] in a week 4 encounter against [[Fatih Karagümrük S.K.|Fatih Karagümrük]] which ended 2–1 to Fenerbahçe.<ref name="2020-21 FB KGMK">{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe-Karagümrük: 2–1|url=https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/fenerbahce-karagumruk-2-1-6321142|publisher=[[Milliyet]]|date=3 October 2020|access-date=7 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201207092205/https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/fenerbahce-karagumruk-2-1-6321142|archive-date=7 December 2020}}</ref> On 6 December 2020, he saved another penalty, from [[Radosław Murawski]], in a week 11 encounter against [[Denizlispor]] which Fenerbahçe won 2–0.<ref name="2020-21 DEN FB (1)">{{cite news|title=Denizli'de Altay'ın Gecesi|url=https://www.trtspor.com.tr/haber/futbol/super-lig/denizlide-altayin-gecesi-222108.html|publisher=[[TRT Spor]]|date=6 December 2020|access-date=7 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201207091833/https://www.trtspor.com.tr/haber/futbol/super-lig/denizlide-altayin-gecesi-222108.html|archive-date=7 December 2020}}</ref> He produced total of seven saves during this game, in which Fenerbahçe were down to 10-men following the sending-off of [[Serdar Aziz]].<ref name="2020-21 DEN FB (2)">{{cite news|title=Süper Lig'de 11'inci haftaya damga vuran 7 olay|url=https://skor.sozcu.com.tr/2020/12/08/super-lig-11inci-haftaya-damga-vuran-7-olay-1547262/|publisher=[[Sözcü]]|date=8 December 2020|access-date=8 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201208124611/https://skor.sozcu.com.tr/2020/12/08/super-lig-11inci-haftaya-damga-vuran-7-olay-1547262/|archive-date=8 December 2020}}</ref>

On 30 October 2021, in a 2–1 away defeat to [[Konyaspor]], Bayındır was injured in a collision with [[Serdar Gürler]] in the 69th-minute and left the field, being replaced by [[Berke Özer]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fenerbahce Altay left the field in tears|url=https://www.livik.net/2021/10/30/fenerbahce-altay-left-the-field-in-tears/|publisher=Livik.net|access-date=18 January 2022|archive-date=1 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901165227/http://ww38.livik.net/2021/10/30/fenerbahce-altay-left-the-field-in-tears/|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, Fenerbahçe made an announcement, saying: “Although no fracture was detected in Altay Bayındır’s shoulder, acromioclavicular separation was observed. It has been decided that our player will undergo surgery and his treatment has started.”<ref>{{cite news|title=Bilgilendirme|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2021-tr/10/bilgilendirme|publisher=[[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]|access-date=18 January 2022|language=tr|archive-date=31 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211031094541/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2021-tr/10/bilgilendirme|url-status=live}}</ref> It was estimated that he would be unavailable for approximately three months.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe'de Konyaspor maçı sonrası Altay Bayındır ve sakatlık şoku! 3 ay yok|url=https://www.fotomac.com.tr/fenerbahce/2021/10/30/fenerbahcede-konyaspor-maci-sonrasi-altay-bayindir-soku-altay-bayindir-3-ay-yok|publisher=Fotomac.com.tr|access-date=18 January 2022|language=tr|archive-date=1 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901165313/https://www.fotomac.com.tr/fenerbahce/2021/10/30/fenerbahcede-konyaspor-maci-sonrasi-altay-bayindir-soku-altay-bayindir-3-ay-yok|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 18 March 2023, Bayındır extended his contract, which was due to expire at the end of [[2022–23 Fenerbahçe S.K. season|the season]], until 2027.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/3/kaptanimiz-altay-bayindir-4-yil-daha-fenerbahcemizde|title=Kaptanımız Altay Bayındır 4 yıl daha Fenerbahçemizde|date=18 March 2023|accessdate=18 March 2023|publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K.|language=tr|archive-date=1 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901165228/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/3/kaptanimiz-altay-bayindir-4-yil-daha-fenerbahcemizde|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 April 2023, he had a [[lumbar hernia]] surgery.<ref>{{cite news|title=Geçmiş Olsun Altay Bayındır|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/4/gecmis-olsun-altay-bayindir|publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K.|access-date=17 April 2023|language=tr|archive-date=1 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901165227/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/4/gecmis-olsun-altay-bayindir|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Manchester United===
On 1 September 2023, Bayındır joined [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on an initial four-year deal, with an option to extend his contract for a further season, making him the first Turkish player to sign for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 September 2023 |title=Altay Bayindir signs for United |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-united-sign-goalkeeper-altay-bayindir-from-fenerbahce-september-2023 |access-date=1 September 2023 |website=Manchester United |language=en-GB |archive-date=1 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901165227/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-united-sign-goalkeeper-altay-bayindir-from-fenerbahce-september-2023 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news |date=1 September 2023 |title=Man Utd sign goalkeeper Bayindir for £4.3m |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66680445 |access-date=1 September 2023 |archive-date=1 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901165455/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66680445 |url-status=live }}</ref> The transfer fee was reported to be £4.3&nbsp;million.<ref name=":2" /> He made his debut on 28 January 2024 in a 4–2 away win against [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]] in the [[2023–24 FA Cup|FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.trtspor.com.tr/haber/futbol/altay-ilk-macina-cikti-manu-kazandi-287751.html |title=Altay ilk maçına çıktı ManU kazandı |trans-title=Altay played his first match, ManU won |publisher=TRT Spor |language=tr |date=28 January 2014 }}</ref>

Bayındır was named as the starting goalkeeper for the [[2024–25 FA Cup|FA Cup]] match against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 12 January 2025, where he made a crucial save from [[Martin Ødegaard]]'s penalty on the 72nd minute. The match headed to the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] after a 1–1 draw after playing for 120 minutes. He made a crucial save against [[Kai Havertz]]'s attempt as Manchester United made it to the fourth round. He was awarded as the [[Man of the Match]] after his performance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cg45q0gd0reo|title='In one week, your life can change' – Man Utd hail 'hero' Bayindir|date=13 January 2025|access-date=13 January 2025|work=[[BBC Sport]]|last=Howell|first=Alex|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250113024300/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cg45q0gd0reo|archive-date=13 January 2025|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 13 April 2025, Bayındır was named in the starting line-up for Manchester United's clash vs [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] as number 1, being his first Premier League match for the club. The game ended 4–1 to Newcastle, with goals from [[Sandro Tonali]], [[Alejandro Garnacho]], [[Harvey Barnes]] and [[Bruno Guimarães]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2025}}

==International career==
===Youth===
Bayındır represented the [[Turkey national under-20 football team|Turkey under-20 team]] at the [[2018 Toulon Tournament]].<ref name="2018 Turkey U20">{{cite news|title=Turkey squad announced for the Toulon Tournament 2018!|url=https://festival-foot-espoirs.com/en/festival/detail_actualite.php?id=2973|publisher=festival-foot-espoirs.com|date=19 May 2018|access-date=5 October 2020|language=Tr|archive-date=6 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200606225218/https://festival-foot-espoirs.com/en/festival/detail_actualite.php?id=2973|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
Bayındır was called-up to the senior [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] by [[Şenol Güneş]] on 9 November 2020, for [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B|UEFA Nations League]] encounters against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] and [[Russia national football team|Russia]].<ref name="2020 senior callup (1)">{{cite news|title= Son dakika: Altay Bayındır A Milli Takım'a çağrıldı|url=https://www.fanatik.com.tr/son-dakika-altay-bayindir-a-milli-takima-cagrildi-2182747|publisher=[[Fanatik (Turkey)|Fanatik]]|date=9 November 2020|access-date=7 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201207093527/https://www.fanatik.com.tr/son-dakika-altay-bayindir-a-milli-takima-cagrildi-2182747|archive-date=7 December 2020}}</ref><ref name="2020 senior callup (2)">{{cite news|title=A Millî Takım'ın Hırvatistan, Rusya ve Macaristan maçları aday kadrosu açıklandı|url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=34079|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|date=9 November 2020|access-date=7 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201207093657/https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=34079|archive-date=7 December 2020}}</ref> He made his senior international debut on 27 May 2021, in a friendly against [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=596343|title=Turkey v Azerbaijan game report|date=27 May 2021|access-date=2 June 2021|archive-date=3 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603033414/https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=596343|url-status=live}}</ref>

